
End-to-End 5G O-RAN Network Setup Guide

Author: M.Sc Manasik Hassan
Date: 2025-07-24
Version: 3.0.0

To set up an E2E 5G O-RAN network, the following components must be installed in the specified order:

1. Open5GS Core
You can set up the Open5GS core either from source or as a containerized version using Docker. Building it from source offers more flexibility, especially when working with multiple gNBs, UEs, and setting up a distributed E2E O-RAN network across different machines.

Follow the detailed instructions provided below: 
https://open5gs.org/open5gs/docs/guide/02-building-open5gs-from-sources/

key steps include:
1.	Install MongoDB
2.	Configure the TUN device
3.	Build Open5GS from source: Make sure to pull the latest version of open5gs source code from GitHub
4.	Configuration:
	Replace the default sample.yaml file located in open5gs/build/configs/ with the one provided with this guideline. 
	Execute the following command from the Open5GS directory to run the core: $ ./build/tests/app/5gc
5.	Add a route to enable UE WAN connectivity. Add the following commands as well for enabling DL Traffic to UE:
	$ sudo iptables -I FORWARD -i ogstun -j ACCEPT
	$ sudo iptables -I FORWARD -o ogstun -j ACCEPT

6.	Build the WebUI for Open5GS to manage subscribers

7.	Register subscriber Information: 
Use the WebUI to add a subscriber. The following details are for a single UE:
	IMSI: 001010000000101
	Ki: 0C0A34601D4F07677303652C0462535B
	Opc: 63BFA50EE6523365FF14C1F45F88737B
	APN: internet

2. O-RAN OSC Near RT RIC

1.	Clone the repository:
$ git clone https://github.com/srsran/oran-sc-ric
$ cd ./oran-sc-ric

2.	Replace the default docker-compose.yml file located in oran-sc-ric/ directory with the version provided with this guideline.

3.	Start the RIC:
$ docker compose up


3. gNB

You can configure the gNB using one of two methods:

Option 1: Using srsgNB and srsUE (No Hardware Required)
This method supports a single point to point gNB-UE connection. For multiple UEs, additional configuration using GNU Radio is required to enable ZeroMQ for multi-point communication.

1.	Follow the instruction provided below for building the srsRAN project with ZeroMQ libraries: 
https://docs.srsran.com/projects/project/en/latest/tutorials/source/near-rt-ric/source/index.html

$ cd build/apps/gnb
$ sudo ./gnb -c gnb_zmq.yaml e2 --addr="10.0.2.10" --bind_addr="10.0.2.1"

2.	If some problems arise when building the srsRAN_Project, please use the following commands: 
$ git clone https://github.com/srsran/srsRAN_Project.git
$ cd srsRAN_Project
$ mkdir build
$ cd build
$ cmake ../ -DENABLE_EXPORT=ON -DENABLE_ZEROMQ=ON -DAUTO_DETECT_ISA=OFF
$ make -j`nproc`

3.	Some issues might appear for Ubuntu 24.04 when trying to build srsRAN_4G project, here is the full set of commands to download the project and compile it instead:
$ sudo apt install gcc-11 g++-11
$ git clone https://github.com/srsRAN/srsRAN_4G.git
$ cd srsRAN_4G
$ mkdir build && cd build
$ export CC=$(which gcc-11)
$ export CXX=$(which g++-11)
$ cmake ../ -B build
$ cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

4.	Configure srsUE: 
	Copy the ue_zmq.conf file provided with this guideline to the /srsRAN_4G/build/build/srsue/src directory

	Run the srsUE with the following command:
$ sudo ip netns add ue1
$ sudo ./srsue ue_zmq.conf  

	Ping from UE to core:
$ sudo ip netns exec ue1 ping -i 0.1 10.45.0.1


Option 2: Using USRPs and Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) UEs
1.	Set Up USRP Drivers:
	Before connecting the USRP device, install the required drivers:
$ sudo apt-get install libuhd-dev uhd-host

	Connect the USRP device via USB 3.0, then run:
$ sudo uhd_images_downloader
$ uhd_find_devices

2.	Missing Libraries:
$ sudo apt-get install libpcsclite-dev libbladerf-dev soapysdr-module-all libsctp-dev libuhd-dev doxygen libdwarf-dev libelf-dev binutils-dev libdw-dev libmbedtls-dev libyaml-cpp-dev lksctp-tools libsctp-dev libconfig++-dev

3.	Configure the gNB:

	Follow the instructions provided here: https://docs.srsran.com/projects/project/en/latest/tutorials/source/near-rt-ric/source/index.html

	Copy the gnb_rf_b200_tdd_n78_20mhz.yml configuration file provided with this guideline to the following directory ./srsRAN_Project/build/apps/gnb/

	Run the gNB with the following command:
$ cd ./srsRAN_Project/build/apps/gnb/
$ sudo ./gnb -c gnb_rf_b200_tdd_n78_20mhz.yml e2 --addr="10.0.2.10" --bind_addr="10.0.2.1"


4. COTS UE
Insert a SIM card with PLMN ID 00101 into a 5G-compatible phone that supports private network PLMN IDs
Make sure internet apn is selected and enabled
Turn on the device and verify its connection to the core. Ensure UL/DL traffic.

5. KPIMON xApp
Follow the xApp installation and setup guidelines available here: https://docs.srsran.com/projects/project/en/latest/tutorials/source/near-rt-ric/source/index.html

NOTE:
If any changes are made to the xApp, such as adding libraries to the python_xapp_runner docker file or making other updates, a new docker image must be built:
$ docker compose build --no-cache python_xapp_runner
$ docker compose up -d python_xapp_runner
$ docker compose exec python_xapp_runner ./kpm_mon_xapp.py

This will enable KPI monitoring for the O-RAN network



